description:
From the minds of illustrators Trudy Cooper and Doug Bayne comes Oglaf, and extremely filthy (and extremely funny) webcomic that tackles sex and fantasy with a satirical bent. There is all sorts of nudity and gay/straight/other? sex, and all of it is in service to the stories and the sticky situations (pun intended). The initial &quot;main&quot; storyline focuses on an apprentice to a sorceress who enjoys torturing him by denying him the right to masturbate, and then forcing him to hose down two hot lesbians as part of his &quot;chores&quot;. Yeah, it gets even weirder and more hilarious from there. There is the plight of the Snow Queen, who needs to be sexually satisfied in order for it to become spingtime - but she freezes everything solid (including her lovers' dicks). Then there is Kronar, Son of Man, a mighty and fearsome warrior who is also a homosexual, and an insatiable one at that. The story of his &quot;son&quot; is particularly hilarious. Or perhaps you will enjoy the tale of a man &quot;cursed&quot; with such amazing sexual prowess that he instantly makes anyone else cum when they come into contact with his penis - but he himself can not get off. Much more filthiness and perversion abound in this terrific gem of a comic, and unlike other sex/adult comics it is not meant to titillate, but rather get you to laugh at all the absurdity. And it works, oh trust me - HOW it works! If you are old enough to enjoy it, this is one of the funniest things you will ever read. Give it a whirl.

I have manually ripped all the images into 6 cbrs, with the website warning as a cover image for each. Each CBR is around 50-70 pages and it reads quick, since it is all single-page panels. Everything is not precisely chronological to the website; the first 3 volumes or issues are organized to make the main plot flow a little better. The remaining three volumes are exactly chronological, though. As I mentioned earlier, there are overarching story arcs interspersed with one-offs or smaller stories, but if you read straight through I don't think it is all that confusing. Hope you dudes and dudettes enjoy this one, and make you sure you check out the main page:

Oglaf.com

